    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-04-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 30, of February 26 last, reporting that you have agreed with your
                    colleagues in the demand to be made of the Chinese Government for a tract of
                    land in Peking for the diplomatic quarter, and that you have called their
                    attention to the inadequacy of the area allotted therein to the United States.
                    You also report that you have expressed the profound regret which this
                    Government and people would feel in learning that any of the powers should have
                    found it necessary, under any circumstances, to dispossess or in any way
                    interfere with the foreign maritime-customs staff.</p>
                <p>Your action in the matter is approved by the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
